# SASS Installation Steps

## Prerequisites
- Node.js (version 20.16 recommended)

## Installation Steps

### Option 1: Using npm (if Node.js is already installed)
```
npm install -g sass
```

### Option 2: Linux installation (Ubuntu)
1. Install Node.js version 20.16 using nvm:
```
curl -o- https://raw.githubusercontent.com/nvm-sh/nvm/v0.39.7/install.sh | bash
```
2. Exit and reopen terminal
3. Install Node.js:
```
nvm install 20.16
nvm use 20.16
```
4. Install SASS:
```
npm install -g sass
```

### Option 3: Windows installation
1. Download and install Node.js from https://nodejs.org/
2. Open PowerShell or Command Prompt as Administrator
3. Install SASS globally:
```
npm install -g sass
```

### Verification
To verify installation, run:
```
sass --version
```

This should display the SASS version number.
